    {
      "source": "hackernews",
      "subsource": "news.ycombinator.com",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "A sleep-like consolidation mechanism for LLMs",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.26099",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48281226",
      "score": 199,
      "comments": 133,
      "author": "juxtapose",
      "published": "2026-05-26T15:36:24Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Idle GPU cycles are leveraged for generative replay, training LLMs on self-generated data to consolidate knowledge and mitigate catastrophic forgetting.",
        "This sleep-like phase stabilizes neural weights via self-distillation or contrastive learning, maintaining performance on historical tasks during continuous learning.",
        "Practitioners can implement this post-training routine during off-peak periods to optimize memory footprint and model weight coherence without retraining."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
